The paper proposes a method for training deep neural networks using distributed optimization over a graph. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of nonlinear functions such as ReLU and DCutLU suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). The application of the method to image processing tasks, as mentioned in the abstract, indicates that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant subcategory. Finally, the use of optimization techniques such as ADMM suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of optimization and control (cs.SI).
